Title : Fermi ball
Text : In [[cosmology]], '''Fermi balls''' are hypothetical objects that may have been created in the early history of the universe by [[spontaneous symmetry breaking]]. One paper has described them as "charged [[SLAC bag|SLAC-bag]] type structures".<ref>{{cite arXiv|eprint= hep-ph/9412264|last1=  Macpherson|first1=  Alick L.|title=  Fermi Ball Detection|last2=   Pinfold|first2=  James L.|date=  1994}}</ref>

